On Monday, March 22, 2004, at 08:13AM, Seann Stafford <seann.stafford(-at-)ints.com> wrote:

>I was afraid to use lubricants on the stars as they sit so close to
>the brake pads.  Never knew of the lithium grease thing.

Copper antiseize is effective. It's thick so it doesn't contaminate the brake shoes. Just put some inside the barrel and on the threads of the adjuster.

It will attract brake dust but it doesn't affect the ability to adjust them easily.

